OL,3,CParents' campaign for safer nurseries
OL,4,Cafter baby's death one step closer
OL,6,FGigi's parents, Katie and John,
OL,7,Flaunched a campaign in June calling
OL,8,Ffor major changes, including
OL,9,Fcompulsory CCTV in nurseries,
OL,10,Fmandatory safe sleep training for
OL,11,Fstaff and unannounced inspections by
OL,12,FOfsted to be routine.
OL,14,FIn a letter, and following their
OL,15,Fmeeting in London with Early Years
OL,16,Fminister Stephen Morgan, he said
OL,17,F"ensuring the safety of children is of
OL,18,Futmost importance to both the
OL,19,Fdepartment and me."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
